HEADWORD: Neurocord
<hw>Neu"ro*cord</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Neuro-</ets>
+ <ets>cord</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A cordlike organ
composed of elastic fibers situated above the ventral nervous cord of
annelids, like the earthworm.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Neu`ro*cor"dal</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

